---
/**
 * context-engineering 0002 · Figure 3 — the hero "two-stage retrieval pipeline".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0002-context-selection-and-retrieval.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block at
 * the top of the document <body>. The markers this figure references (arw, arwM)
 * are inlined into its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 300"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Query fans into BM25 and vector search, results are fused, a cross-encoder re-ranks, top-k enter the window."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >TWO-STAGE RETRIEVAL &mdash; recall first, then precision</text
        >

        <!-- query -->
        <rect x="262" y="32" width="116" height="32" rx="7" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Query</text
        >

        <!-- stage 1 label -->
        <text x="150" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#6b675f"
            >STAGE 1 &mdash; recall · cheap · wide</text
        >

        <!-- BM25 + vector -->
        <rect x="60" y="92" width="180" height="40" rx="7" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="150" y="111" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Lexical (BM25)</text
        >
        <text x="150" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >exact terms &amp; identifiers</text
        >
        <rect x="400" y="92" width="180" height="40" rx="7" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="490" y="111" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Semantic (vector)</text
        >
        <text x="490" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >meaning &amp; synonyms</text
        >

        <!-- query to both -->
        <line x1="290" y1="64" x2="180" y2="90" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="350" y1="64" x2="460" y2="90" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- fuse -->
        <rect
            x="220"
            y="160"
            width="200"
            height="38"
            rx="7"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="178" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Fuse (RRF / weighted)</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="191" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >one candidate list</text
        >
        <line x1="150" y1="132" x2="270" y2="158" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="490" y1="132" x2="370" y2="158" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- stage 2 label -->
        <text x="320" y="222" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#6b675f"
            >STAGE 2 &mdash; precision · expensive · top-N only</text
        >

        <!-- rerank -->
        <rect x="220" y="228" width="200" height="38" rx="7" fill="#efe7f0" stroke="#111110"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="246" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Cross-encoder re-rank</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="259" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >re-score top-N jointly with query</text
        >
        <line x1="320" y1="198" x2="320" y2="226" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>

        <!-- window -->
        <rect
            x="455"
            y="228"
            width="130"
            height="38"
            rx="7"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="520" y="250" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >top-k &rarr; window</text
        >
        <line x1="420" y1="247" x2="453" y2="247" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Stage 1 (lexical + semantic, fused) maximizes <b>recall</b> cheaply across many candidates. Stage
        2 (cross-encoder) maximizes <b>precision</b> on the top-N only — it cannot recover anything stage
        1 missed.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r2">2</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
